<img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.bellanaija.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/maxresdefault-18.jpg?ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Marley family and Amplified Music have reimagined Bob Marley’s iconic song, “One Love” in support of UNICEF’s coronavirus response. This new version features members of the Marley family as well as artists from various parts of the world, such as Patoranking, Cedella Marley, Stephen Marley, Skip Marley, Dawtas of Aya, Jason Tamba, Natty, Raja Kumari and many more. Also featured in the video are Alexander Goodeve-Docker, Damascus Voice, Jason Kwan, Kehlani Reid, Nyahla Asante, Desire, Marshae, Margo Chalmers amongst others. This remake was produced by Stephen Marley, Gil Cang, video director and edited by Jamie Thomas. This global project is raising funds to support children most affected by COVID-19 in developing countries, where help is urgently needed. Find out more about the project and how you can support oneloveoneheart.org. Watch the video below: The post Here’s the Remake of Bob Marley’s Iconic Song “One Love” feat. The Marleys, Patoranking & Natty appeared first on BellaNaija – Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.